//@version=6
// =============================================================================
// Overnight Gap on High Volume — Pine Script v6
//
// Spots an opening gap between two specific 5-minute candles:
//
//   * the LAST bar of one trading session  (the "previous" candle), and
//   * the FIRST bar of the next session    (the "open" candle).
//
// Two conjunctive conditions, evaluated on the first 5m bar of a new session:
//
//   1. Opening gap   — the open candle gaps away from the prior session's last
//                      close by at least a configurable percentage. Gap up
//                      (open > prevClose) is detected by default; gap down can
//                      be enabled via input, and gap up can be disabled.
//   2. Huge volume   — the prior session's LAST 5m bar carried volume that is
//                      large relative to recent activity: its volume >= a
//                      multiple of the average 5m bar volume over a lookback.
//
// When both hold, a PINK triangle is drawn BELOW the open candle (where the
// gap appears).
//
// Apply on a 5m intraday chart. The session model keys off the daily timeframe
// change (timeframe.change("1D")), matching the day boundaries used elsewhere
// in this module (see breakout-detection.pine).
// =============================================================================
indicator("Overnight Gap on High Volume (Blue Star)", overlay = true, max_bars_back = 5000)

// --- Tunables ----------------------------------------------------------------
MIN_GAP_PCT       = input.float(0.5, "Min opening gap %",            minval = 0.0, step = 0.1)
ALLOW_GAP_UP      = input.bool(true,  "Detect gap up")
ALLOW_GAP_DOWN    = input.bool(false, "Detect gap down")
VOL_LOOKBACK_BARS = input.int(50,    "Volume lookback (5m bars)",    minval = 1)
VOL_MULTIPLIER    = input.float(3.0, "Huge-volume multiple of avg",  minval = 1.0, step = 0.5)

// -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
// Detect the first bar of a new session. timeframe.change("1D") is true on the
// bar whose day differs from the previous bar's day — i.e. the session's open.
// -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
newSession = timeframe.change("1D")

// -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
// Carry forward the prior session's LAST bar (the "previous" candle). On every
// bar we remember the values of the bar that just closed; when a new session
// starts, the [1] reference points at the final bar of the prior session.
//   prevClose  — close of the prior session's last 5m bar
//   prevVolume — volume of that same bar
// -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
prevClose  = close[1]
prevVolume = volume[1]

// =============================================================================
// 1. Opening gap — the new session's open vs the prior session's last close.
// =============================================================================
gapPct      = na(prevClose) or prevClose == 0 ? na : (open - prevClose) / prevClose * 100.0
gappedUp    = ALLOW_GAP_UP   and not na(gapPct) and gapPct >=  MIN_GAP_PCT
gappedDown  = ALLOW_GAP_DOWN and not na(gapPct) and gapPct <= -MIN_GAP_PCT
openingGap  = gappedUp or gappedDown

// =============================================================================
// 2. Huge volume on the prior session's last bar.
//   Baseline = average 5m bar volume over the preceding VOL_LOOKBACK_BARS bars,
//   measured up to (and excluding) the prior session's last bar — i.e. ta.sma
//   of volume one bar back. The last bar is "huge" if it is at least
//   VOL_MULTIPLIER times that baseline.
// =============================================================================
avgVol     = ta.sma(volume, VOL_LOOKBACK_BARS)[1]
hugeVolume = not na(prevVolume) and not na(avgVol) and avgVol > 0 and
     prevVolume >= avgVol * VOL_MULTIPLIER

// =============================================================================
// Final signal — only on the first bar of a new session, both conditions true.
// =============================================================================
detected = newSession and openingGap and hugeVolume

// --- Plotting / alerts -------------------------------------------------------
plotshape(detected, "Overnight gap", shape.triangledown, location.belowbar,
     color = color.new(color.fuchsia, 0), size = size.small)
alertcondition(detected, "Overnight gap on high volume", "Overnight gap: {{ticker}}")
